.TH "ccio_alloc" 9 "ccio_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ccio_alloc \- Allocate a consistent DMA mapping.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" ccio_alloc
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma_handle "  ","
.BI "gfp_t flag "  ","
.BI "unsigned long attrs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The PCI device.
.IP "size" 12
The length of the DMA region.
.IP "dma_handle" 12
The DMA address handed back to the device (not the cpu).
.IP "flag" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "attrs" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function implements the pci_alloc_consistent function.
